olive oil
1 carrot
1 capsicum
1 sachet Tex-Mex spice blend
1 packet Chicken Breast
2 Flatbread
1 packet Baby Leaves
pinch Chilli Flakes
drizzle vinegar (balsamic or white wine)
1 packet Smokey Aioli

• Preheat oven to 220°C/200°C fan-forced.
• Cut carrot and capsicum into bite-sized chunks.
• Place veggies on a lined oven tray. Drizzle with olive oil and toss to coat. Spread out evenly, then roast until tender, 25-30 minutes.

Little cooks: Kids can help toss the veggies.

• In a medium bowl, add Tex-Mex spice blend and a drizzle of olive oil. Add chicken breast, turning to coat.
• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat. Cook chicken, turning, until browned, 2 minutes each side.
• Transfer chicken to a second lined oven tray and bake until cooked through, 8-12 minutes.

TIP: Chicken is cooked through when it's no longer pink in the middle.

• Meanwhile, drizzle (or brush) each flatbread with olive oil and season with salt.
• When veggies have 5 minutes cook time remaining, return frying pan to medium-high heat. Cook flatbreads until golden and warmed through, 1-2 minutes each side.
• When roasted veggies are done, add baby leaves, chilli flakes (if using) and a drizzle of vinegar and olive oil to the tray. Gently toss to combine.

• Slice chicken. Tear flatbreads into 3cm pieces (or squares).
• Divide Tex-Mex chicken, roast veggie toss and flatbreads between bowls.
• Serve with smokey aioli. Enjoy!

Little cooks: Kids can take the lead and dollop over the smokey aioli when serving!